ozwell.s1: The two notes are very similar. Both describe the case of a 77-year-old Japanese man with a history of right alar swelling and pain, suspected malignancy, and severe pulmonary dysfunction due to recurrent end-stage lung cancer. They detail the findings of a submucosal tumor in the right nasal vestibule, the results of a biopsy and CT scan, and the patient's medical history, including previous lung cancer surgery. Both notes outline the treatment plan involving minimally invasive surgery under local anesthesia to relieve nasal pain and improve quality of life, and they describe the surgical findings and post-operative course. Additionally, both notes mention the follow-up findings of maxillary bone metastasis from lung carcinoma.
